<item>
            <title>[JCR-242] registration of new namespace does not respect existing session mappings</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-242</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>consider the following (starting with a default namespace registry):&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
// remap nt namespace&lt;br/&gt;
Session.setNamespacePrefix(&amp;quot;foobar&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.jcp.org/jcr/nt/1.0&quot;&gt;http://www.jcp.org/jcr/nt/1.0&lt;/a&gt;&amp;quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
// create new namespace&lt;br/&gt;
NamespaceRegistry.registerNamespace(&amp;quot;foobar&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.foo.org/bar/1.0&quot;&gt;http://www.foo.org/bar/1.0&lt;/a&gt;&amp;quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
now the session used above that remapped the nt namespace has an ambigous namespace mapping:&lt;br/&gt;
foobar --&amp;gt; &amp;quot;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.jcp.org/jcr/nt/1.0&quot;&gt;http://www.jcp.org/jcr/nt/1.0&lt;/a&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;quot;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.jcp.org/jcr/nt/1.0&quot;&gt;http://www.jcp.org/jcr/nt/1.0&lt;/a&gt;&amp;quot; --&amp;gt; foobar&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;quot;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.foo.org/bar/1.0&quot;&gt;http://www.foo.org/bar/1.0&lt;/a&gt;&amp;quot; --&amp;gt; foobar&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
i.e. the new foobar namespace is hidden for this session. either the registration should not work, or an automatic prefix is to be defined in all local session mappings.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
